## Troubleshooting Process

1. Check interface
2. Check IP
3. Check Gateway
4. Ping Gateway
5. Ping Internet
6. Verify DNS
7. Trace Route
8. Identify Root Cause
1. Verify network interface.

```bash
ip addr
```

2. Verify routing table.

```bash
ip route
```

3. Test gateway.

```bash
ping <gateway-ip>
```

4. Test Internet connectivity.

```bash
ping 8.8.8.8
```

5. Verify DNS.

```bash
nslookup google.com
```

6. Trace the network path.

```bash
tracepath google.com
```

## Best Practice

Follow a structured process rather than guessing. Record each observation before moving to the next step.
